io.smint.clapi.consumer.integration.core.jobs.impl

Class AssetConverter

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.smint.clapi.consumer.integration.core.jobs.impl.BaseSyncDataConverter<ISmintIoAsset,ISyncAsset>
      • io.smint.clapi.consumer.integration.core.jobs.impl.AssetConverter

  • public class AssetConverter
extends BaseSyncDataConverter<ISmintIoAsset,ISyncAsset>
    Converts an instance from ISmintIoAsset to ISyncAsset.

    Conversion involve the replacement of Smint.io specific ID with synchronization target keys. Hence this implementation makes use of an instance of ISyncTarget to do translation of the IDs.

    New instances to ISyncLicenseTerm are created utilizing ISyncTarget.createSyncLicenseTerm().

      • convert

        public ISyncAsset[] convert(ISmintIoAsset rawAsset)
        Description copied from class: BaseSyncDataConverter
        Converts a single raw instance of FromType to a new instance of ToType.

        Usually a one-to-one conversion is performed, so the result should be an array with just one element. But sometimes, a direct mapping is impossible (eg: converting assets). Then more than a single element will be returned in the resulting array.

        Specified by:
        convert in class BaseSyncDataConverter<ISmintIoAsset,ISyncAsset>
        Parameters:
        rawAsset - the source instance to convert.
        Returns:
        a list if new instance with converted data or null if source is null.
